'''Eskilstuna Municipality''' (''Eskilstuna kommun'') is a [[municipalities of Sweden|municipality]] in [[Södermanland County]] in southeast [[Sweden]], between [[Lake Mälaren]] and [[Lake Hjälmaren]]. The seat of the municipality is in the [[city status in Sweden|city]] of [[Eskilstuna]].
The present municipality was formed in 1971 by the merger of the City of Eskilstuna, the City of Torshälla and five rural municipalities.
==Localities== *[[Alberga, Sweden|Alberga]] *[[Borsökna]] *[[Bälgviken]] *[[Eskilstuna]] (seat) *[[Hållsta]] *[[Hällberga]] *[[Hällbybrunn]] *[[Kjulaås]] *[[Mesta, Sweden|Mesta]] *[[Kvicksund]] (partly in [[Västerås Municipality]]) *[[Skogstorp, Eskilstuna Municipality|Skogstorp]] *[[Torshälla]] *[[Tumbo]] *[[Ärla]]
